What is Amazon EC2?

Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) is a web service providing resizable compute capacity in the cloud. It enables users to rent virtual servers, called "instances," to run their applications. EC2 revolutionizes computing economics by allowing users to pay only for the capacity they use, eliminating upfront hardware investment.

Virtual Servers (Instances)

  • â€¢ Virtual servers located in AWS data centers.
  • â€¢ Supports Linux, Windows, and macOS.
  • â€¢ Discrete units with CPU, memory, and storage.

Amazon Machine Images (AMIs)

An AMI serves as a template containing the software configuration (OS, application server, applications) to launch an instance. Use pre-built or create your own custom AMIs.

Elastic Block Store (EBS)

Persistent block-level storage volumes for EC2 instances. Data remains even if the instance is terminated. Highly available and durable with various SSD and HDD performance options.

Security & Accessibility

Security Groups

Virtual firewalls controlling inbound and outbound traffic. Define protocols, ports, and IP ranges for precise control.

Key Pairs

Secure connection mechanism using private keys for SSH (Linux) or administrative passwords (Windows).

Scalability & Availability

Auto Scaling

Automatically adjusts instance counts based on demand to maintain performance while minimizing costs during low traffic.

Elastic Load Balancing

Distributes incoming traffic across multiple instances to ensure high fault tolerance and application availability.

Regions & Availability Zones

AWS infrastructure is divided into global Regions containing isolated Availability Zones (AZs). This architecture ensures that failures in one location don't compromise the entire application.

Flexible Pricing Models

On-Demand

Pay-as-you-go. No commitments. Ideal for unpredictable workloads.

Reserved

Up to 75% discount for 1-3 year commitments. Best for steady-state usage.

Spot

Up to 90% discount. Bidding on unused capacity. For fault-tolerant apps.

Dedicated

Physical servers exclusively for your use. For specific compliance/licensing.

Benefits of EC2

  • Elasticity: Rapid scale-up/down.
  • Cost-Effectiveness: Pay only for what you use.
  • Flexibility: Choice of OS, CPU, RAM.
  • Reliability: Robust AWS global infrastructure.

Common Use Cases

Web Servers Containerization Big Data Gaming Enterprise CRM Media Streaming Dev/Test

In essence, Amazon EC2 is a fundamental AWS compute service offering exceptional flexibility, scalability, and cost efficiency for running diverse applications in the cloud.
